    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-03T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-03T21:00:00-05:00" n="128"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d128">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">561.333D3/7–344: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-03T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 3, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2048. From White<note n="28" xml:id="d128fn28">Telephoned by Ivan B. White from
                        Bretton Woods, New Hampshire.</note> for Donnelly.<note n="29"
                        xml:id="d128fn29">Walter J. Donnelly, Counselor of Embassy for Economic
                        Affairs in Brazil.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Representatives of the Department and other interested agencies have
                        reached an understanding with Souza Costa<note n="30" xml:id="d128fn30"
                            >Reference is to the Memorandum of Understanding signed at Bretton
                            Woods, N.H., July 4; text transmitted to Rio de Janeiro in airgram
                            A–932, July 6, <ref target="#pg_632">p. 632</ref>.</note> under which
                        the National Coffee Department will assure the sale of 1,500,000 bags of
                        suitable quality coffee for August shipment to the United States, 1,000,000
                        of which will be for the armed forces. In addition, Brazil has assured the
                        sale of a total of 1,000,000 bags monthly of suitable quality for the months
                        September through December.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>In order to meet Army requirements and to avoid rationing, it is
                        imperative that this program be executed expeditiously and in full.</item>
                </list>
                <p>Souza Costa has informed National Coffee Department of the above and is awaiting
                    latter’s confirmation that program will be met. Please keep in close touch with
                    Guedes and trade and inform Department by telegram of prospects for execution of
                    understanding. [White.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
